1
00:00:15,958 --> 00:00:17,458
The thing is...

2
00:00:17,541 --> 00:00:21,250
...I've been scouted, so I'm
going to make my solo debut.

3
00:00:23,458 --> 00:00:27,125
[YUU]
No. What's she saying?

4
00:00:27,208 --> 00:00:29,750
This can't be real.

5
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:30,875
[NACHI]
Damn it!

6
00:00:30,958 --> 00:00:33,291
Haruna, c'mon! Say something!

7
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:40,375
I've gotta take a step
toward my dream.

8
00:00:40,458 --> 00:00:42,416
I'm sorry, guys.

9
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:45,583
Which means I'm gonna
have to quit the band.

10
00:00:45,666 --> 00:00:46,750
[gasps]

11
00:00:49,291 --> 00:00:50,708
[NACHI]
Come on, man!

12
00:00:50,791 --> 00:00:52,458
What can I say?

13
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:54,916
She's already made her decision.

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,291
It's over.

15
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:00,791
[YUU]
Isn't it...?

16
00:01:17,875 --> 00:01:19,166
<i>The place that I always dreamed</i>

17
00:01:19,250 --> 00:01:22,125
<i>I'd reach one day</i>
<i>is too high above us</i>

18
00:01:22,208 --> 00:01:23,208
<i>To get to</i>

19
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,375
<i>The promise we made is fading</i>

20
00:01:25,458 --> 00:01:28,500
<i>every moment we</i>
<i>conform like they do</i>

21
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:29,875
<i>I wanna move on my own</i>

22
00:01:29,958 --> 00:01:31,250
<i>Step away from the crowd</i>

23
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:32,708
<i>I wanna dance to my own beat</i>

24
00:01:32,791 --> 00:01:35,083
<i>I'm done trying to blend in</i>

25
00:01:36,291 --> 00:01:38,875
<i>I won't be tied</i>
<i>to a tedious world</i>

26
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:41,708
<i>Repeating each day like</i>
<i>a broken record sickens me</i>

27
00:01:41,791 --> 00:01:44,250
<i>(No matter how I try</i>
<i>I can't escape repetition)</i>

28
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,375
<i>It's hard to change it up</i>

29
00:01:45,458 --> 00:01:46,958
<i>When no one else is listening</i>

30
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:48,750
<i>We're in a box, stuck in a box</i>

31
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:51,333
<i>Meant to stifle what we feel</i>

32
00:01:51,416 --> 00:01:54,083
<i>Forced to erase all</i>
<i>that we know is real</i>

33
00:01:54,166 --> 00:01:55,333
<i>But I refuse to be locked up</i>

34
00:01:55,416 --> 00:01:56,416
<i>Won't live in this prison</i>

35
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:58,333
<i>Gotta fight for open skies</i>

36
00:01:59,541 --> 00:02:01,125
<i>Time to break free</i>

37
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:05,083
<i>Open our hearts to a world and</i>
<i>go racing forward to the light</i>

38
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:06,791
<i>These broken chains</i>
<i>can't hold us back</i>

39
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:10,791
<i>We're finally on track to heal</i>
<i>all the fractures in ourselves</i>

40
00:02:10,875 --> 00:02:12,166
<i>As we climb and ascend</i>

41
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:13,500
<i>Aiming high to the end</i>

42
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:15,958
<i>We'll feel a climber's high</i>

43
00:02:16,041 --> 00:02:18,791
<i>Hear these words and know your</i>
<i>dream can be stronger than steel</i>

44
00:02:18,875 --> 00:02:20,000
<i>Just believe</i>

45
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:20,791
<i>You have the power</i>

46
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:24,416
<i>Let your voice be heard</i>

47
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:29,458
♪

48
00:02:31,875 --> 00:02:33,750
[AKIRA]
That's our standard contract.

49
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:35,375
Have your parents look
it over and let me know

50
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:37,458
if they have any questions.

51
00:02:37,541 --> 00:02:38,875
[FUUKA]
Okay.

52
00:02:40,583 --> 00:02:43,333
[AKIRA] You seemed
so sure when you said no.

53
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:44,708
That's kind of you.

54
00:02:44,791 --> 00:02:48,375
Sorry, but my place
is with my bandmates.

55
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:50,250
So, what made
you change your mind?

56
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:59,250
[AKIRA] "A maiden's heart
is as fickle as autumn."

57
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:01,916
Actually, that's about
first love, isn't it?

58
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,416
I thought about it and decided

59
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:05,208
this was the right choice.

60
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:07,750
Good. Then I'm glad
we can agree.

61
00:03:09,041 --> 00:03:11,125
Thank you
for everything, sir.

62
00:03:18,416 --> 00:03:21,250
[phone buzzes]

63
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,000
[KOYUKI]
Hey, it's me!

64
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:27,125
Oh, gosh, you're not
in class right now, are you?

65
00:03:27,208 --> 00:03:29,583
[YUU]
No, school's out.

66
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,250
What time is it there? 

67
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:33,125
[KOYUKI]
Seven in the morning.

68
00:03:33,208 --> 00:03:35,958
I think I'm finally
getting over my jet lag.

69
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,333
Good thing, too,
because we're filming

70
00:03:37,416 --> 00:03:39,041
a music video today.

71
00:03:39,125 --> 00:03:41,125
[YUU]
That's great. Good luck.

72
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:44,541
Nico, is there something wrong?

73
00:03:44,625 --> 00:03:46,166
[YUU]
No, not really.

74
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:49,750
[KOYUKI] You sure? You sound
a little bit down today.

75
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:51,916
[YUU]
Nah, I'm okay.

76
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,791
[KOYUKI] I've bought
a ton of souvenirs.

77
00:03:53,875 --> 00:03:56,375
I hope I'll see you
as soon as I get back.

78
00:03:56,458 --> 00:03:57,458
[YUU]
Yeah.

79
00:03:57,541 --> 00:03:59,625
[KOYUKI]
Hey, are you really all right?

80
00:03:59,708 --> 00:04:00,916
Did something happen?

81
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,333
[YUU]
No, nothing.

82
00:04:02,416 --> 00:04:03,916
[KOYUKI]
Well, if you're sure.

83
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,708
I just can't wait to see
your face after so long.

84
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:08,208
Talk to you soon, okay?

85
00:04:08,291 --> 00:04:09,375
[YUU]
Sure.

86
00:04:24,458 --> 00:04:25,916
[MIKASA]
Wow, it's been a while.

87
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,583
Feels like forever
since we've met up.

88
00:04:28,666 --> 00:04:30,625
That's because there's
no point in meeting up.

89
00:04:30,708 --> 00:04:33,541
What's a band without a vocalist
supposed to do, anyway?

90
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:34,875
Or are we actually
going to discuss

91
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,833
finding a new one?

92
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:38,625
We can't do that.

93
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:41,000
You know there's
no replacement for Fuuka.

94
00:04:41,083 --> 00:04:43,833
[NACHI] I agree. So, then,
what's the point of this?

95
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,208
[MIKASA]
It just...

96
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:47,500
...doesn't feel right for it
to fizzle out this way

97
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:49,083
with no closure at all.

98
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,666
Okay, so you need to
hear the words out loud?

99
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,875
Fine, we're breaking up!

100
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,958
[SARA]
Would you stop it?

101
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:57,916
You're not helping
anything, you know.

102
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:01,625
That talk about
creating a legend.

103
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:04,041
I'd actually started
to believe what she said.

104
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:07,166
I tried so hard
to get Fuuka to join the

105
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:11,166
track team, but she managed
to drag me into a band instead.

106
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:12,541
Crazy.

107
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:15,333
But, honestly, I think
I was looking for something.

108
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:17,125
As you know,
track was pretty much

109
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,708
my whole life before this.

110
00:05:19,791 --> 00:05:21,833
Truth is, things haven't
gone all that

111
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:23,500
well for me in school.

112
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:25,250
So, when I look
back on it now,

113
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,875
it seems obvious that
the band was an escape.

114
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,375
[SARA]
An escape from what?

115
00:05:29,458 --> 00:05:33,083
Well, from disappointed
expectations, I guess.

116
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:37,666
Turns out, there
are still some track

117
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:40,416
scholarships available and my
coach even said he'd be happy to

118
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,375
put in a good word for me.

119
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:43,916
He was glad
I came back, and seems

120
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,458
to think my running still has
some potential for success.

121
00:05:47,541 --> 00:05:50,208
And so it's time
to stop playing around.

122
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:52,458
I'm gonna do what
my coach suggests...

123
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:53,875
...and be happy.

124
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:58,500
Time to stop
playing around. Maybe...

125
00:05:58,583 --> 00:06:00,250
...it's not bad advice.

126
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:01,750
Perhaps I should
take it, myself.

127
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:02,791
[gasps]

128
00:06:04,791 --> 00:06:07,291
God, Haruna. Why are
you just standing there?

129
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:09,541
Don't you have a single
thought in your damn head?

130
00:06:09,625 --> 00:06:12,916
[growls] Don't you? What were
you even thinking that night?

131
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,625
Only you could've stopped her!
Are you that blind?

132
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:16,833
--[YUU gasps]
--[MIKASA] Nachi, come on.

133
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,083
[SARA]
Stop it!

134
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:22,041
Hell. Not like
it really matters,

135
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:24,083
but I'm officially done
with this band.

136
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:28,708
[YUU sighs]

137
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:31,625
[FUUKA] ♪ Don't care how
far away we might be ♪

138
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:33,500
♪ Whatever we're both doing ♪

139
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:35,208
♪ We'll never be apart ♪

140
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,083
♪ No matter how hard we try ♪

141
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:39,125
♪ We'll always have each other ♪

142
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,166
♪ A shoulder-- ♪

143
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,375
Wow, that was
absolutely fantastic!

144
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:47,666
Such great work!

145
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,458
Thanks, I'm glad
you're happy with it.

146
00:06:49,541 --> 00:06:52,875
I gotta admit, when I
get it right, I get it right.

147
00:06:54,458 --> 00:06:55,750
[FUUKA]
This is all good.

148
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:59,375
I made the right decision--
it's gonna be okay.

149
00:07:08,958 --> 00:07:11,875
[HISA grunts]
Hey. Have a good shower?

150
00:07:11,958 --> 00:07:14,375
Hey, Brother,
what're you doing home?

151
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:16,833
[HISA] I came by to
pick up some scores.

152
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:17,916
[SARA] Does that mean
the Hedgehogs are

153
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,666
getting back together?

154
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:22,125
Looks like it,
now that those two are back.

155
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:23,791
[SARA]
Good for you.

156
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:24,916
[HISA]
Hmm?

157
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:31,750
Sara, would you
be interested in subbing

158
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,458
for other bands?

159
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:34,916
[SARA gasps]

160
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,958
[HISA] There's a band that
comes into the studio a lot.

161
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:38,875
They have an important gig
coming up but one of their

162
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,791
members got injured.

163
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:42,083
[SARA sighs]

164
00:07:42,166 --> 00:07:45,541
So, they're looking
for a guitarist right now.

165
00:07:45,625 --> 00:07:47,875
[SARA]
I don't know.

166
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:49,666
[HISA]
Yeah, I didn't think so.

167
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,583
You're not the type to
be happy as long as you get

168
00:07:51,666 --> 00:07:53,166
to play a few gigs.

169
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:58,166
[SARA]
No, wait. I'll give it a try.

170
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:01,125
[gasps]
What? Are you serious?

171
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:03,583
Yeah, and what's
with the reaction?

172
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:05,625
It was your idea, after all.

173
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:08,541
I know! I know
it was, but I guess I...

174
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:10,916
You just answered
so quickly, so...

175
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,166
Well, look. To be honest...

176
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,791
...I feel bad about
the way it all went down.

177
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:17,000
I was the one who
introduced them to

178
00:08:17,083 --> 00:08:19,333
each other, Fuuka and Mogami.

179
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:24,000
Doesn't matter, she
decided for herself in the end.

180
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:26,708
Fuuka is responsible
for her own choices.

181
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:32,875
[MIKOTO] Makoto, are you
really sure about this?

182
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:33,875
About what?

183
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:35,541
I mean, you moved
out because you

184
00:08:35,625 --> 00:08:38,125
wanted to pursue
your music, isn't that right?

185
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:39,708
[MIKASA sighs]

186
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:41,666
[MIKOTO] But if you're
coming back home,

187
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,625
that means you're throwing away
your dream and following

188
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:46,750
the path Dad decides
for you, doesn't it?

189
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:50,375
I hate to see you give
up and decide to admit defeat!

190
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:52,833
Listen to me, Mikoto.

191
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:55,541
It's not always about
winning and losing.

192
00:08:55,625 --> 00:08:57,375
I finally realized.

193
00:08:57,458 --> 00:09:00,333
I never even tried to convince
Dad of my point of view.

194
00:09:00,416 --> 00:09:02,041
I just ran away instead.

195
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:05,416
[MIKOTO] But, the piano!
Your dream of playing music!

196
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:06,833
What about that?

197
00:09:11,666 --> 00:09:13,500
[door creaks]

198
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:15,291
[YUU]
Huh? Tama?

199
00:09:15,375 --> 00:09:18,583
[giggles] I was determined
to surprise you.

200
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:19,833
Did it work?

201
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:24,750
[YUU]
This really is a surprise.

202
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:28,500
[KOYUKI giggles] It's been
a crazy long time, huh?

203
00:09:28,583 --> 00:09:31,958
It was your concert,
the last time I saw you.

204
00:09:32,041 --> 00:09:33,041
[YUU]
That's right.

205
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:34,458
It was such a great show.

206
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:36,375
I was so proud of you.

207
00:09:36,458 --> 00:09:37,666
Thank you.

208
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:41,750
[gasps]
Something did happen, didn't it?

209
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:44,041
[YUU sighs]

210
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:45,666
[CHITOSE] Hey, don't
you think we should take

211
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:47,375
some snacks upstairs to them?

212
00:09:47,458 --> 00:09:49,875
If they want any, Yuu will
come down and get some.

213
00:09:49,958 --> 00:09:51,250
Yeah, he will.

214
00:09:51,333 --> 00:09:53,458
I think maybe I'll go ahead
and bring some up there.

215
00:09:53,541 --> 00:09:54,916
Would you forget it?

216
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,083
They're together in their
own little world right now.

217
00:09:57,166 --> 00:09:59,541
Don't barge in.
Let them enjoy it.

218
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:01,208
[whines]

219
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:06,208
[KOYUKI]
So, Fuuka's moving on?

220
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:09,541
[YUU] Yeah, I think
what really hurts is that

221
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,791
none of us saw this coming.

222
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,166
So, now, the rest of us

223
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,041
have kind of lost
our motivation.

224
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:20,458
It's like a hole just
opened up right inside my chest.

225
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:21,708
[KOYUKI sighs]

226
00:10:21,791 --> 00:10:24,000
Now I realize, the heart
and soul of this band

227
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:26,125
really was Akitsuki.

228
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,583
So if she isn't in it
anymore, there's really

229
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:30,500
no point in keeping it going.

230
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:34,708
[KOYUKI] But maybe
this is all for the best.

231
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:35,875
[gasps]

232
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:38,666
Even if The Fallen
Moon might be gone,

233
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:41,125
you can still keep
pursuing music.

234
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,125
Huh?

235
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:43,666
[KOYUKI]
Did you forget?

236
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,916
We made a promise to each other
that we'd stand on the same

237
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,041
stage together someday.

238
00:10:48,125 --> 00:10:50,583
Yeah. And as much
as I appreciate

239
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:53,791
you bringing that up right now.
I'm not ready to play--

240
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,375
I don't care about all that!

241
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:56,791
[gasps]

242
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,333
[KOYUKI]
Don't you see?

243
00:10:58,416 --> 00:11:00,791
All I've ever cared about
is being with you.

244
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,625
It's all I want.
