245
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,541
Tama, wait.

246
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:14,333
I love you
and I always have, my Nico.

247
00:11:14,416 --> 00:11:15,541
That's why...

248
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:19,000
[gasps]

249
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,166
Tama, don't do this.

250
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,416
[KOYUKI]
Why not?

251
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,041
Well, because I...

252
00:11:34,666 --> 00:11:35,583
[YUU]
I'm sorry.

253
00:11:35,666 --> 00:11:37,125
[gasps]

254
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:45,000
[sighs]
I knew all along.

255
00:11:46,916 --> 00:11:48,541
[KOYUKI]
I knew it couldn't be me.

256
00:11:51,291 --> 00:11:52,625
What do you mean?

257
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:55,583
I knew it all,
the feelings you didn't

258
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:58,000
know you had for Fuuka.

259
00:11:58,083 --> 00:12:01,125
And the feelings she
didn't know she had for you.

260
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:03,250
All of it.

261
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:07,041
[sobs]
So, listen, Nico.

262
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:14,958
Just be honest
with yourself from now on.

263
00:12:15,041 --> 00:12:16,208
Tama!

264
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:28,291
[KOYUKI sobs]

265
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:30,375
[KOYUKI]
Goodbye, Nico.

266
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:47,583
I don't need one.

267
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:49,083
So, you can go ahead
and keep 'em both.

268
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:51,958
I can't! It's a bonus
for "couples only"!

269
00:13:04,541 --> 00:13:06,958
[HIBIKI]
Yuu! The bath is free!

270
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,875
[HIBIKI]
Are you deaf or what?

271
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:13,208
Hello? Can you hear me?

272
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:19,416
[MAYA]
How did he look?

273
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,833
He's sitting at
his desk working really

274
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:22,958
intently on something.

275
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:25,875
[CHITOSE] What is it?
What's he working on?

276
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:27,708
I have no idea.

277
00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:30,000
He hasn't eaten
anything today, either.

278
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:31,458
I'm getting worried about him.

279
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:33,208
[gasps]
I bet I know what it is!

280
00:13:33,291 --> 00:13:35,791
Koyuki must have dumped him!

281
00:13:35,875 --> 00:13:38,166
[HIBIKI] Well, I think
he'll be just fine.

282
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,750
[BOTH gasp]

283
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:40,958
Those were the eyes
of a guy who's

284
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:43,916
looking forward to
something. You'll see.

285
00:13:53,083 --> 00:13:57,625
♪

286
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:01,291
[SARA sighs]

287
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,750
[GUITARIST A] Wow, I can totally
see why Hisashi recommended you!

288
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:05,125
I know that you were
only supposed to be

289
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:06,666
helping us out
with this one gig,

290
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:08,166
but would you want
to join the band?

291
00:14:08,250 --> 00:14:10,375
--Huh?
--Seriously, we sound

292
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:12,416
a bazillion times better
with you playing!

293
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,875
[BASSIST A]
Yeah, for real.

294
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:16,375
Welp, we can talk
about it again after the gig!

295
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:17,791
--Yeah!
--[GUITARIST A] Cool!

296
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:25,166
[NACHI pants]

297
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:28,291
[MIYAMOTO] So, Nachi? What do
you think of college practices?

298
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:30,666
Honestly, it's all
I can do just to keep up.

299
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:33,000
But I'm enjoying it!

300
00:14:33,083 --> 00:14:35,416
[MIYAMOTO]
Hmph. I see.

301
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:36,708
Once you enroll,
you'll be dedicating

302
00:14:36,791 --> 00:14:40,041
a lot more time to track.
I hope you're ready.

303
00:14:40,125 --> 00:14:41,416
I am!

304
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,375
[MIKASA sighs]

305
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:01,125
[YUU groans]

306
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:08,000
Okay!

307
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:11,833
[NACHI]
Why are you doing here so early?

308
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:16,500
[YUU] Because... I want the
band to get back together.

309
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:20,416
Why are you
doing this? It's too late.

310
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,250
Yeah, I get it. But, I--

311
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,958
Enough. I told
you man, I'm gonna

312
00:15:25,041 --> 00:15:27,666
focus on track from now on.

313
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:30,000
[YUU] Please, just listen
to this, would you?

314
00:15:30,083 --> 00:15:31,333
Then we'll talk again!

315
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:33,166
[NACHI grunts]
Hey!

316
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:38,500
[YUU]
Haah.

317
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:41,833
[MIKASA]
Yuu?

318
00:15:45,708 --> 00:15:47,916
[YUU]
I want the band to keep going.

319
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,916
With you in it.

320
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,208
[gasps]

321
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,875
[gasps]

322
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:56,791
I'm sorry, Yuu.

323
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:59,916
Moving out of my father's house
was an act of rebellion.

324
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,458
But now,
that has to be over.

325
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:03,708
[gasps]

326
00:16:03,791 --> 00:16:06,083
I've decided
to listen to my father.

327
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:09,000
I mean, he's literally
promised me a happy future!

328
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:11,291
So I don't have to
stress myself out any more.

329
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:15,416
Chasing pointless dreams that
won't come true, anyway!

330
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:17,583
Listen, I know it's unfair.

331
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:19,833
I have no right to
interfere in your future.

332
00:16:19,916 --> 00:16:22,750
I know it's a lot to ask.

333
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:25,750
But, my friend,
I'm asking you, anyway.

334
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:28,375
Help me put this band
back together again.

335
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:29,583
[MIKASA sighs]

336
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:32,166
[YUU]
Here.

337
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:40,375
[BAND MEMBERS laughing]

338
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:41,833
[BASSIST A]
Man, we killed it today!

339
00:16:41,916 --> 00:16:43,750
[DRUMMER A]
I know, right?

340
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:52,875
So you really wrote
this song for the band?

341
00:16:52,958 --> 00:16:58,458
[YUU] Yes. Sara, I'm putting
the band back together.

342
00:17:00,041 --> 00:17:01,458
[YUU]
Please come back.

343
00:17:03,958 --> 00:17:06,291
I'm really happy
that you asked.

344
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:09,208
But I'm already...

345
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:11,416
I do believe, it's
thanks to all of you that

346
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:14,166
I'm able to get along
so well with these guys.

347
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,500
I'm truly thankful
to you for that.

348
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:18,583
And I know I always will be.

349
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:23,625
But, I... think it's
best if I stay where I am.

350
00:17:23,708 --> 00:17:25,666
I understand that.

351
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:28,458
But even so,
I refuse to give up.

352
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:32,958
[SARA sighs]

353
00:17:33,041 --> 00:17:35,416
[door bell ringing]

354
00:17:39,958 --> 00:17:42,250
[door bell continues ringing]

355
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:09,625
[YUU] Hey, guys.
This is a song I wrote.

356
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:12,000
I know I don't express
my feelings much.

357
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:16,125
[YUU] But this song
is honest, from my heart.

358
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:19,750
Would you do me a favor
and please give it a listen?

359
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:23,250
And if you feel anything
like me after you do,

360
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:25,958
meet me at 3 on Saturday
at our favorite place.

361
00:18:29,291 --> 00:18:32,041
[pants]

362
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,916
[NACHI sighs]

363
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:38,916
You coming?

364
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,291
[NACHI]
Uh... Yes!

365
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:47,125
[door bell rings]

366
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,208
Yeah?

367
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:49,791
Umineko Movers!

368
00:18:49,875 --> 00:18:52,083
Thanks for helping out,
I appreciate it.

369
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:56,208
[footsteps]

370
00:18:56,291 --> 00:18:58,000
[gasps]

371
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,416
[YUU]
Sara!

372
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:04,250
Aren't the others here?

373
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,125
Their loss.

374
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:07,833
I'm so glad
you're here, though!

375
00:19:09,416 --> 00:19:11,583
Your lyrics got me.

376
00:19:11,666 --> 00:19:13,916
They spoke to me
in a very real way.

377
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,208
[gasps]

378
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:19,958
[MIKASA]
So sorry I'm late!

379
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,375
I had to cancel
quite a few things

380
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:23,291
before I could make it here!

381
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:25,791
The three of us, huh?

382
00:19:25,875 --> 00:19:29,333
Well. I'd say that's pretty good
since it's so last-minute!

383
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:31,500
Don't make him
feel bad, Mikasa!

384
00:19:31,583 --> 00:19:32,833
Not what I meant.

385
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:37,541
[MIKASA] I wrote sheet
music of your song.

386
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:39,041
Thanks, man.

387
00:19:39,125 --> 00:19:40,750
[NACHI]
Hey!

388
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:44,583
Who gave your permission to get
things moving before I got here?

389
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:47,416
I listened and it was hot!

390
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,291
Thank you so much, my friend.

391
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:51,666
Come on.

392
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,666
You wouldn't have gotten
anywhere without me, right?

393
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:55,416
So? Where's our singer?

394
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:58,208
Yeah. I reached
out to Akitsuki, too.

395
00:19:58,291 --> 00:19:59,750
[SARA]
Hmm?

396
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:02,125
[YUU] I know it's selfish
of me, but she just has

397
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:04,708
to be a part of The Fallen Moon.

398
00:20:04,791 --> 00:20:07,916
It's hers. So I'm determined
to bring her back.

399
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,083
[MIKASA, SARA grunt]

400
00:20:09,166 --> 00:20:10,833
Well then, we'd best
start practicing so

401
00:20:10,916 --> 00:20:13,250
we'll be ready for her
when she comes back!

402
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,583
[YUU]
Right!

403
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:20,708
♪

404
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:51,750
[KOYUKI giggles]
So, you're starting it up again?

405
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:54,875
[YUU] Yeah. Except,
we're still waiting

406
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,708
for Akitsuki to come back.

407
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:02,750
Tama, thanks so much.

408
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:06,166
Because of you,
I was able to take this step.

409
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:07,875
You made me believe I could.

410
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:10,500
[gasps]
I dunno.

411
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:14,083
I'm pretty sure you already knew
what mattered to you.

412
00:21:14,166 --> 00:21:17,333
You didn't need me
to realize that.

413
00:21:17,416 --> 00:21:19,208
I'm sorry.

414
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:20,666
Don't apologize.

415
00:21:24,791 --> 00:21:26,041
[KOYUKI giggles]

416
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:31,791
[KOYUKI] Thanks for
everything, old friend.

417
00:21:35,958 --> 00:21:37,125
[KOYUKI giggles]

418
00:21:50,916 --> 00:21:53,541
<i>Looking up at the sky</i>
<i>I felt an emptiness</i>

419
00:21:53,625 --> 00:21:56,458
<i>All the colors of</i>
<i>summer have been faded</i>

420
00:21:56,541 --> 00:22:00,083
<i>Before I even knew the things</i>
<i>that made me the happiest</i>

421
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:02,083
<i>Were hidden and tucked away</i>

422
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:04,916
<i>But when I looked at you</i>
<i>it all felt so intense</i>

423
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,791
<i>Your eyes cut to the</i>
<i>core of my existence</i>

424
00:22:07,875 --> 00:22:11,250
<i>Every word that you spoke</i>
<i>was like a painting in every hue</i>

425
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,083
<i>You brought calm into my world</i>

426
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:15,625
<i>All I can do now is breathe</i>

427
00:22:15,708 --> 00:22:18,583
<i>And figure out just what I need</i>

428
00:22:18,666 --> 00:22:21,166
<i>Resolve myself, pursue my dreams</i>

429
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:23,708
<i>I'm running</i>

430
00:22:23,791 --> 00:22:26,500
<i>Moving forward, taking your hand</i>

431
00:22:26,583 --> 00:22:27,875
<i>Being with you</i>

432
00:22:27,958 --> 00:22:29,541
<i>I'm finally free enough to</i>
<i>spread out my wings</i>

433
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:32,041
<i>Let's catch the wind</i>
<i>and go for a ride</i>

434
00:22:32,125 --> 00:22:35,958
<i>You and I can fly</i>
<i>anywhere together</i>

435
00:22:36,041 --> 00:22:38,375
<i>We can go as high</i>
<i>up as we want</i>

436
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:41,208
<i>Following the path that's</i>
<i>been laid pout before us</i>

437
00:22:41,291 --> 00:22:44,791
<i>Guided by our</i>
<i>bonded hearts forever</i>

438
00:22:44,875 --> 00:22:48,208
<i>Let's keep living</i>
<i>out this fantasy</i>

439
00:22:48,291 --> 00:22:52,208
<i>And chasing our dreams</i>

440
00:22:52,291 --> 00:22:55,541
<i>Ah... Ah...</i>

441
00:22:55,625 --> 00:23:00,583
♪

442
00:23:14,125 --> 00:23:16,250
[doorbell rings]

443
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:18,666
[SUZUKA]
Coming!

444
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:22,291
A-ha! You wouldn't be Yuu
Haruna, now, would you?

445
00:23:22,375 --> 00:23:24,875
Uh. Yes, I am.

446
00:23:24,958 --> 00:23:26,666
Hi, there, I'm Fuuka's mom.

447
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:28,000
Nice to meet you.

448
00:23:28,083 --> 00:23:29,625
[YUU]
Nice to meet you, too.

449
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:32,000
Um, is Akitsuki here?

450
00:23:32,083 --> 00:23:34,125
[SUZUKA] Sorry,
Fuuka's out for the night.

451
00:23:34,208 --> 00:23:36,291
She told me she'd
be back pretty late.

452
00:23:36,375 --> 00:23:38,875
[YUU]
Oh, okay. Thank you.

453
00:23:38,958 --> 00:23:40,750
Could you tell her
I'll come back later?

454
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:41,875
[SUZUKA]
Sure.

455
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:43,666
Thanks. Well, goodnight, then.

456
00:23:52,083 --> 00:23:54,750
All right,
I sent him away for you.

457
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:57,666
Thanks, Mom. I'm sorry.

458
00:23:57,750 --> 00:24:00,666
Are you sure
it's what you want?

459
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:04,083
Yeah. Yeah, I'm sure.

460
00:24:13,541 --> 00:24:15,458
[FUUKA]
Next time, "Fair Wind"

